    <stitle>New Vehicle Processing Manual - Undecking and Storage - UNDECKING AND STORAGE - UNDECKING EQUIPMENT
        MAINTENANCE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
        <title>UNDECKING EQUIPMENT MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Carrier drivers are instructed to not use unsafe or outdated undecking equipment. If Dealer
                        facilities are not adequate, the Carrier is authorized to engage proper facilities or services
                        and to apply the tariff charge to the Dealer.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>It is extremely important that undecking equipment be properly maintained by the dealer or
                        consignee.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>
                <hotlnk document="s10005_6.xml" xrefid="f1000502">Undecking Sling</hotlnk>, ZTSE4280
            </title>
            <para>BEFORE EVERY USE, inspect the sling and all fastenings and attachments for damage and defects. DO NOT
                USE the sling if you find any of the following problems:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Acid or caustic burns</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Melting or charring of any part of the sling surface</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Snags, punctures, tears or cuts</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Broken or worn stitches</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Distortion of fittings or chains</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>If any of the above conditions are found, replace it through International's tool supplier, or repair
                and re-certify the sling. The following locations are able to service slings:
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">U.S.:</emph>
            </para>
